name: brent_nf_cc
description: brentlab processing with the dev branch version of the nf-core callingcards

name: chipexo_pugh_allevents
description: this data was pulled from the yeastepigenome.org site. The allevents data was extracted and minimally processed for upload. see https://github.com/cmatKhan/parsing_yeast_database_data
citation: Venters BJ, Wachi S, Mavrich TN, Andersen BE, Jena P, Sinnamon AJ, Jain P, Rolleri NS, Jiang C, Hemeryck-Walsh C, Pugh BF. A comprehensive genomic binding map of gene and chromatin regulatory proteins in Saccharomyces. Mol Cell. 2011 Feb 18;41(4):480-92. doi: 10.1016/j.molcel.2011.01.015. PMID: 21329885; PMCID: PMC3057419.

name: harbison_chip
description: This data is pulled from the Young lab website. See https://github.com/cmatKhan/parsing_yeast_database_data for parsing details
citation: Harbison CT, Gordon DB, Lee TI, Rinaldi NJ, Macisaac KD, Danford TW, Hannett NM, Tagne JB, Reynolds DB, Yoo J, et al. 2004. Transcriptional regulatory code of a eukaryotic genome. Nature 431: 99–104.doi:10.1038/nature02800

name: hu_reimann_tfko
description: This is the Hu TFKO data which was reprocessed by Reiman et al (see citation) and then minimally parsed for the DB. See https://github.com/cmatKhan/parsing_yeast_database_data
citation: Reimand J, Vaquerizas JM, Todd AE, Vilo J, Luscombe NM. Comprehensive reanalysis of transcription factor knockout expression data in Saccharomyces cerevisiae reveals many new targets. Nucleic Acids Res. 2010 Aug;38(14):4768-77. doi: 10.1093/nar/gkq232. Epub 2010 Apr 12. PMID: 20385592; PMCID: PMC2919724.

name: kemmeren_tfko
description: This data was pulled from https://deleteome.holstegelab.nl/. See https://github.com/cmatKhan/parsing_yeast_database_data/blob/main/R/parse_kemmeren_data.R for parsing details
citation: Kemmeren P, Sameith K, van de Pasch LA, Benschop JJ, Lenstra TL, Margaritis T, O'Duibhir E, Apweiler E, van Wageningen S, Ko CW, et al. 2014. Large-scale genetic perturbations reveal regulatory networks and an abundance of gene-specific repressors. Cell 157: 740–752.doi:10.1016/j.cell.2014.02.054

name: mcisaac_oe
description: This data is pulled from the Calico website. the Raw & processed gene expression data was used and minimally processed for upload. See https://github.com/cmatKhan/parsing_yeast_database_data/blob/main/R/parse_mcisaac_data.R
citation: Hackett SR, Baltz EA, Coram M, Wranik BJ, Kim G, Baker A, Fan M, Hendrickson DG, Berndl M, McIsaac RS. 2020. Learning causal networks using inducible transcription factors and transcriptome-wide time series. Mol Syst Biol (in press).

name: brent_mitra_cc
description: brentlab data processed with the mitra pipeline
